element.name: Marnocks Cache by Windsockers, Traditional Cache (1/1.5)

long-description.p: The name Portmarnock originated from Irish meaning port, and St.Marnock who arrived there in the fifth century. Marnock a missionary of St.Patrick, also associated with Kilmarnock in Scotland, converted the local Celts from worshiping Water, Trees, and Wells, to Christianity. (Tendencies that are still prevalent today if you observe the inhabitants fancy gardens!) Being politically correct Marnock blessed the Druid Well and it became the Holy Well. The ruins of Marnock's church are still to be seen in the graveyard
The Cache is a decon container please take care retrieving and replacing the cache and beware of the golfing muggles
